## Developer Guide

If you are new to using `nbdev` here are some useful pointers to get you
started.

### Install GSGSolveitTest in Development mode

``` sh
# make sure GSGSolveitTest package is installed in development mode
$ pip install -e .

# make changes under nbs/ directory
# ...

# compile to have changes apply to GSGSolveitTest
$ nbdev_prepare
```

## Usage

### Installation

Install latest from the GitHub
[repository](https://github.com/gsgbills/GSGSolveitTest):

``` sh
$ pip install git+https://github.com/gsgbills/GSGSolveitTest.git
```

or from [conda](https://anaconda.org/gsgbills/GSGSolveitTest)

``` sh
$ conda install -c gsgbills GSGSolveitTest
```

or from [pypi](https://pypi.org/project/GSGSolveitTest/)

``` sh
$ pip install GSGSolveitTest
```

### Documentation

Documentation can be found hosted on this GitHub
[repository](https://github.com/gsgbills/GSGSolveitTest)’s
[pages](https://gsgbills.github.io/GSGSolveitTest/). Additionally you
can find package manager specific guidelines on
[conda](https://anaconda.org/gsgbills/GSGSolveitTest) and
[pypi](https://pypi.org/project/GSGSolveitTest/) respectively.
